05  Development Action Items & Deployment Strategy

Ten action items, prioritized for the engineering team. Each maps to a specific AEGIS-X system component with deployment notes.
#
Action Item
P
Owner
Deployment Notes
01
Cloud provider API connectors — AWS Config, GCP SCC, Azure Defender with unified event schema
P0
Backend / Cloud Eng.
Schema versioning from day one. Provider connectors deploy as independent microservices — failure in one must not degrade others.
02
OPA/Rego policy engine — rule versioning, rollback, dry-run mode before live enforcement
P0
Security Eng.
Dry-run is non-negotiable at launch. Deploy policy engine behind feature flag — enforce in observe mode first, enforce-and-act second.
03
Weighted severity scoring algorithm — asset criticality x compliance exposure x provider severity
P0
Backend / Data Eng.
Algorithm must be transparent and auditable — publish scoring logic in docs. Deploy score recalculation as async job triggered by scan completion.
04
Immutable audit log pipeline — append-only store, tamper-evident hash chain, queryable API
P0
Backend / Security
Hash chain must be verifiable by third-party auditors. Deploy to isolated append-only data store — no service account with delete permissions.
05
Findings table API — sort, filter, pagination supporting 10k+ findings at sub-500ms response
P1
Backend / Frontend
Performance baseline before launch. Index on severity + account + timestamp. Use cursor-based pagination — offset pagination fails at scale.
06
Compliance mapping layer — tag every finding to NIST CSF, FedRAMP, EU AI Act, STAR CAR-D controls
P1
Compliance Eng.
Must support multiple simultaneous framework mappings per finding. Deploy as a tag-enrichment service that runs post-scan, not inline with detection.
07
RBAC layer — security engineer / CISO / auditor / read-only views with field-level permissions
P1
Platform / Auth Eng.
Auditors must not modify findings — separation of duties is a compliance requirement. Integrate with existing SSO/IdP. Role definitions must be configurable, not hardcoded.
08
Remediation executor — one-click action with before/after state capture and 15-minute rollback window
P2
Backend / Cloud Eng.
Deploy behind explicit user-opt-in flag. Rollback window is hard requirement. Every action writes to audit log before execution begins, not after.
09
Audit export engine — PDF and JSON compliance report generation from finding + remediation chain
P2
Backend / Platform
PDF formatted for direct FedRAMP submission — no post-processing by the user. JSON for machine ingestion by downstream GRC tools.
10
Posture score trend API — time-series store for score history, delta calculation, and alert thresholds
P2
Data Eng.
Score history drives the CISO reporting layer in the next phase. Store as immutable time-series — scores are never updated, only appended.


